{
  "texts": [
    "More practical applications, both for AI systems in general and particularly for LLMs, could emerge in training contexts.",
    "Training on interactions with AI systems is likely to become widespread soon at various levels, both educational and professional, to ensure the correct use of these systems in compliance with safety and social interaction standards in the workplace.",
    "This area would be particularly relevant for Human Resources.",
    "In general terms, incorporating devices, even virtual ones, into AI systems to express scales of assessment of the intelligence expected by the user can generate a continuously updated set of data.",
    "This data can be utilized from historical and aggregate perspectives, benefiting not only the system producer but also third-party control authorities."
  ]
}